      • getByEmpId

        public EmpSchedule getByEmpId​(int empId)
                       throws NotFoundException
        Returns an employee's schedule by given employee id. If there are no employee's schedule by the specified employee id in a data base then returns new employee's schedule which the employee by specified id based. If there no department' schedule in the data base then returns new employee's schedule: employee-field is initialized by specified empId, start work time, end work time, start lunch time and lunch time are nulls.
        Specified by:
        getByEmpId in interface EmpScheduleService
        Parameters:
        empId - the employee id.
        Returns:
        the employee schedule by given employee id. null if there are no employee schedule with the employee id.
        Throws:
        NotFoundException - if there are no employee by specified id in the data base.
